postcontent: This is a new  Pre-War Winchester 71 Deluxe 24" rifle in .348 with long tang and short comb! The quality of the pre-war rifles, the fit of the wood the finish, and overall internal machinery is a superb time in history for Winchester. This rifle was the rifle to do all the things the 1886 and 1895 Winchesters did, all in one amazingly designed cartridge, the .348 Winchester. Built with Winchester proof steel, the rifle could handle greater cartridge pressures, as well as retain better bluing during heavy use. For those who hunt large game such as elk, moose, bear, etc, this is the rifleman’s rifle. The 4 digit serial number, 26xx, dates this rifle to second year production, 1936. Overall, the rifle condition is excellent, with the blued finish retained better than 94%, with thinning on underside of receiver and lever. The remaining receiver and barrel finish is strong, but thinning intermittently. The stock is solid with over 92% finish remaining. There is some wear at the heel of the butt stock, and intermittent handling marks around the stock and fore end as noted in the photos. The lock up is tight and bore excellent on this rifle. It will make a superb collector piece for Winchester lever gun collectors!

title: For Sale:  Winchester 1873 Saddle Ring Carbine SRC in 44 WCF 44-40 Antique 1886
postcontent: Offered for your consideration is this vintage Winchester 1873 saddle ring carbine made in 1886. It's in the sought after 44-40 caliber and has the standard 20 inch carbine barrel. The bore is exceptionally good for a 131 year old carbine, I'd rate the bore a solid 8 to 8.5 on a 10 scale. The rifling is still nice and sharp, there is very, very light scattered pin point pitting in the grooves but overall a great shootable bore! The front sight is the standard post style, the rear sight is the Winchester #44A "ladder style" flip up. The sight is intact and fully functional, the elevation slide holds position as it should from top to bottom adjustment. The finish on the barrel, magazine tube and receiver is a fairly even dark plum blue.
